1. *Novčanik* mi je ispao na ulici. (My *wallet* fell out of my pocket on the street.)
2. Kada idem u kupovinu, uvek nosim *novčanik* sa sobom. (When I go shopping, I always carry my *wallet* with me.)
3. Nisam siguran koliko imam novca u *novčaniku*. (I'm not sure how much money I have in my *wallet*.)
4. Moram da kupim novi *novčanik*, stari je potpuno iznošen. (I need to buy a new *wallet*, the old one is completely worn out.)
5. Ostavila je svoj *novčanik* kod kuće, pa nije mogla da plati ručak. (She left her *wallet* at home, so she couldn't pay for lunch.)
6. Otkrio je da mu je *novčanik* ukraden dok je bio u gužvi u gradskom prevozu. (He discovered that his *wallet* was stolen while he was in a crowd on public transport.)
7. Izvadio je parče papira iz *novčanika* i zapisao svoj broj telefona. (He took a piece of paper out of his *wallet* and wrote down his phone number.)
8. Svake večeri pre spavanja, stavljam *novčanik* na noćni stočić. (Every night before bed, I put my *wallet* on the bedside table.)
9. Nije mi bilo dovoljno novca u *novčaniku* da kupim ono što sam planirao. (I didn't have enough money in my *wallet* to buy what I had planned.)
10. Kada mi je prijatelj vratio dug, stavio sam novac direktno u *novčanik*. (When my friend returned the money he owed me, I put it directly into my *wallet*.)